    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\n* The sponsors page is currently the only [content page](https://github.com/neovim/neovim.github.io/tree/master/content) that is not in markdown but html.\n* Sponsors are listed on both the [homepage](https://neovim.io) and on the [sponsors page](https://neovim.io/sponsors/), but there is no overlap. This makes it unclear which sponsors are still currently sponsoring Nvim\n  * Homepage: SerpApi, greptile, CodeRabbit\n  * Sponsors page: Meta, Rizin, Route4Me, Original fundraisers: DigitalOcean, SuperJer, Bountysource, Ryan Durk\n* Need [manual updating](https://github.com/neovim/neovim.github.io/commit/abc11b50d7523cbce6183903d1b8dab06835f5fb) when term ends\n\n\n### Solution\n- [ ] Convert `/sponsors/` to markdown\n- [ ] Create a `data/sponsors.yml` file to track sponsors\n\t- [ ] Can still differentiate in which pages (homepage or sponsor page) to target\n\t- [ ] Can include an end-date which excludes the sponsor from the website during build time \n\n## Questions\n- What's the idea with the two locations? Do we want `/sponsors/` to include all sponsors, and highlight some on the homepage?",
    "closed_at": null,
    "closed_by": null,
